Hi.  I think that a user of a commercial mail provider ought to be able to
have an Internet Domain Name System (DNS) mailbox that is independent of
the commercial provider's name.  For example, i ought to be able to have
the mailbox "JON@POSTEL.MDR.CA.US" even if my mailbox was purchased from 
MCI-Mail.

I would have to have the DNS data base have the record:

		POSTEL.MDR.CA.US	MX	MCI-MAIL.COM

And "MCI-MAIL.COM" would have to be a host on the Internet (there must be
an A record for it).  Further there would have to be a table or information
of some sort in that host that mapped "JON@POSTEL.MDR.CA.US" into the 
MCI-Mail maibox address "107-8243" and forwarded my mail there.

--jon.

